\n","Of course, our product might be zero. Since the log of zero is undefined, let's just add a small positive constant to shift the product away from zero:\n","\n","$$h(n_1, n_2, \\ldots, n_{10}) = \\log( n_1 n_2 \\cdots n_{10} + 0.1 )$$\n","\n","This function $h(n_1, \\ldots, n_{10})$ is what we want to _maximize_, and its negative $-h(n_1, \\ldots, n_{10})$ is what we want to _minimize_.\n","\n","The frequency distribution on states now becomes\n","$$p(n_1, n_2, \\ldots, n_{10}) = e^{-h(n_1, \\ldots, n_{10})/\\sigma^2} = e^{-\\log(n_1n_2\\cdots n_{10} + 0.1)/\\sigma^2}.$$\n","This is good. Python should be able to evaluate this frequency on any state and obtain a positive number.\n","\n","Now we can define our function to minimize in Python:\n"]},{"metadata":{"id":"bx8RISvgfsH8","colab_type":"code","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":85},"outputId":"20b9cac1-7124-4093-dbdb-2533b9fbc77e","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1556731242911,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":315,"user":{"displayName":"Zhaoliang Zhou","photoUrl":"","userId":"11420802199847110781"}}},"cell_type":"code","source":["def func(state):\n","  return -1*math.log(np.prod(state) + 0.1) # +0.1 to avoid log of 0\n","\n","# test the function\n","print(func(testState))\n","print(func(state))\n","\n","# frequency distribution \n","print(math.exp(func(testState)/sig2))\n","print(math.exp(func(state)/sig2))"],"execution_count":26,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","text":["-22.43046691816404\n","-22.77530740445048\n","3.852298302110314e-98\n","1.2248889194751659e-99\n"],"name":"stdout"}]},{"metadata":{"id":"xYtLIDmgo2iW","colab_type":"text"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Proposal transition\n","\n","Next, we need to decide how to propose a transition from a state to a new state.\n","Again, a state is a set of $m=10$ numbers that sum to $N=100$. \n","\n","Here is one approach. If $(n_1, n_2, \\ldots, n_{10})$ is the current state, then we can propose to transition to a new state as follows.\n","\n","* Randomly pick two indexes $i,j \\in \\{1, 2, \\ldots, 10\\}$.\n","* If $n_i > 0$, then let \n","    - $n_i = n_i - 1$\n","    - $n_j = n_j + 1$\n","* If $n_i = 0$, then do nothing.\n","\n","For example, suppose $(13, 6, 0, 16, 14, 9, 17, 6, 10, 9)$ is the current state. Randomly select, say, $i=1$ and $j=4$. In this case, we decrease $n_1$ by $1$ and increase $n_4$ by $1$. The new state becomes $(13, 5, 0, 16, 15, 9, 17, 6, 10, 9)$.\n","\n","If we select $i=2$ and $j=4$, then the new state is the same as the current state, since we can't decrease $n_2 = 0$.\n","\n","Here is an implementation. Run this several times to see it in action."]},{"metadata":{"id":"iPhvgepsKj1X","colab_type":"code","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":68},"outputId":"19cfd870-a7e8-4481-a11a-0a761e380a0c","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1556731432790,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":416,"user":{"displayName":"Zhaoliang Zhou","photoUrl":"","userId":"11420802199847110781"}}},"cell_type":"code","source":["print(\"state:    \", state)\n","indexes = random.sample(range(m),2)\n","print(\"indexes:  \", indexes)\n","if state[indexes[0]] > 0:\n","  state[indexes[0]] = state[indexes[0]] - 1\n","  state[indexes[1]] = state[indexes[1]] + 1\n","print(\"new state:\", state)"],"execution_count":27,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","text":["state:     [10, 12, 12, 7, 13, 11, 6, 10, 10, 9]\n","indexes:   [5, 9]\n","new state: [10, 12, 12, 7, 13, 10, 6, 10, 10, 10]\n"],"name":"stdout"}]},{"metadata":{"id":"EypBG5mrp-W5","colab_type":"text"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Now package this code in a function:"]},{"metadata":{"id":"9dCQIv8Bp2nm","colab_type":"code","colab":{}},"cell_type":"code","source":["def proposal(currState):\n","  propState = currState.copy()\n","  indexes = random.sample(range(m),2)\n","  \n","  if state[indexes[0]] > 0:\n","    propState[indexes[0]] = propState[indexes[0]] - 1\n","    propState[indexes[1]] = propState[indexes[1]] + 1\n","  \n","  return propState"],"execution_count":0,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"id":"oDDQFQUjqpYU","colab_type":"text"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Now we can write the `doMove` function. Note that it looks very much like our `doMove` function from last time."]},{"metadata":{"id":"08SQeAlFqZaD","colab_type":"code","colab":{}},"cell_type":"code","source":["sig2 = 0.1\n","\n","def doMove(currState, sig2):\n","  # propose a move\n","  propState = proposal(currState)\n","  \n","  # get the function value difference\n","  dFunc = func(propState) - func(currState)\n","  \n","  # calculate rho and make a move based on the result\n","  rho = math.exp(-dFunc/sig2)\n","  rand = random.random()    # random number between 0 and 1\n","  if rand < rho:\n","    # then propState will be the new state\n","    return propState\n","  # otherwise, no transition\n","  return currState"],"execution_count":0,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"id":"vEgOuHCt8BjL","colab_type":"text"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Test our function:"]},{"metadata":{"id":"rXORKZ5U8EPS","colab_type":"code","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":85},"outputId":"56676020-6425-4b19-87e6-cd2f3f3022a0","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1556731504035,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":330,"user":{"displayName":"Zhaoliang Zhou","photoUrl":"","userId":"11420802199847110781"}}},"cell_type":"code","source":["print(state)\n","state = doMove(state,sig2)\n","print(state)\n","state = doMove(state,sig2)\n","print(state)\n","state = doMove(state,sig2)\n","print(state)"],"execution_count":30,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","text":["[10, 12, 12, 7, 13, 10, 6, 10, 10, 10]\n","[10, 12, 12, 7, 13, 10, 7, 9, 10, 10]\n","[10, 12, 11, 7, 14, 10, 7, 9, 10, 10]\n","[10, 12, 11, 8, 13, 10, 7, 9, 10, 10]\n"],"name":"stdout"}]},{"metadata":{"id":"qtWz4pg48USs","colab_type":"text"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Simulated annealing\n","\n","Now we can use the simulated annealing process to try to find a state that maximiz